# hexa-lang /.own — project-local SSOT layer, self-hosting only
# 포맷: raw-format (hive /.raw 와 동일 파서). 자세한 스펙: self/raw_loader.hexa
# 검증: ./build/hexa_stage0 tool/own_lint.hexa
#
# Scope (post 2026-04-26 cleanup):
#   hexa-lang/.own retains ONLY self-hosting rules — i.e. constraints
#   that exist precisely because hexa-lang implements the raw-format
#   parser FOR every other repo. Operational policies (cache GC,
#   naming reconciliation, follower-pattern) were either retired,
#   promoted to hive canonical, or moved out of project-local scope.
#
# Removed in this cleanup (audit trail in commit message):
#   own 2 aot-cache-policy        — implementation detail; not self-host
#   own 4 naming-canonical        — historical (.commands->.command
#                                   reconciliation already landed)
#   own 5 raw-ref-follower        — cross-repo policy; belongs in hive
#                                   canonical .raw, not hexa-lang local

own 1 live "parser format stability — raw_loader.hexa is API contract"
  slug parser-format-stability
  scope self/raw_loader.hexa
  why raw_loader.hexa is consumed by hive + nexus + airgenome + (self). Parser surface changes break cross-repo SSOT parsing — backward-compat semver applies.
  enforce-os chflags uchg self/raw_loader.hexa (release via sudo chflags nouchg + tool/emergency/raw_sudo_unlock.sh)
  enforce-agent ~/.claude/settings.json PreToolUse Edit|Write matcher on self/raw_loader.hexa — block w/o semver bump in commit message
  enforce-lint tool/parser_format_stability_lint.hexa (API surface diff vs git baseline + semver guard; exit 1 on breaking change without major bump)
  severity block

own 3 live "hexa-lang self-host fixpoint — parser-owner consumes own format"
  slug hexa-lang-self-host
  decl self/raw_loader.hexa
  scope hexa-lang/.own (after 2026-04-26 migration: .raw retired to hive; .doc dropped from acceptance test because raw_loader's header-kind whitelist [raw|own|ext|roadmap|loop|chain|checkpoint] does not include doc — extending the whitelist is a future surface change governed by own#1)
  why hexa-lang implements raw_loader.hexa — the parser FOR self-format DSL. raw_loader.hexa MUST round-trip parse self-host files as the implementation acceptance test.
  proof tool/own_self_host_lint.hexa
  enforce-os chflags uchg .own (release via sudo chflags nouchg)
  enforce-agent ~/.claude/settings.json PreToolUse Edit|Write matcher on hexa-lang/.own — post-edit raw_cli verify; rollback + block on FAIL
  enforce-lint tool/own_self_host_lint.hexa (calls raw_loader validate_strict + load_raw_file on each target; exit 1 on any non-zero verify)
  severity block
  migrated-from raw 1 hexa-lang/.raw 2026-04-26
